HealthExport Remote lets you visualize your health data on a customizable dashboard accessible from a browser on your computer. You can also perform remote CSV exports on the website. Health data is automatically synced to the service multiple times per day in the background, so there is no need for opening the app on your phone anymore. The data is end to end encrypted between your phone and your browser, thus nobody except you can read it. Note that HealthExport Remote requires a monthly subscription payment due to monthly fees associated with running the service.

Health data types are divided into three categories:
1. Aggregation based types (e.g step count)
2. Record based types (e.g body mass)
3. Workouts and workout routes

Aggregation based types can be exported with aggregation by hours, days, or months. The export of record based types contains all entries from the Health app.

Health Export is compatible with the Shortcut app, thus you can integrate your health data into any automated workflow.

I think your privacy is very important, thus I do not collect any of your health data and I do not share your health data with any analytics provider.

Portion Tracker was designed to help you become more conscious of how much you eat.  We all have tried counting calories, but it simply takes up too much of our time to count every single thing we eat.  Instead, with Portion Tracker, you only count portions.

Portion Tracker is a simplistic approach that is focused more on consistency rather than accuracy as it only takes about 20 seconds to track a whole meal.  However, those 20 seconds will give you a good idea of how much you're eating throughout the day so you can adjust accordingly.
